OL,3,C'Lack of action over spice use' at HMP
OL,4,CParc, inquest hears
OL,6,FIt would create a smell like burned
OL,7,Fpaper, and Mr Appleby would usually go
OL,8,Fto sleep after using it. He told the
OL,9,Fcourt that "after a while" it made him
OL,10,Fnot want to share a cell with him.
OL,12,FMr Winter said he didn't tell officers
OL,13,Fabout Ross Appleby's use of spice
OL,14,Fbecause he didn't think they would
OL,15,Ftake action.
OL,17,F"Loads in there smoke spice" he said.
OL,18,F"And nothing gets done, so I didn't
OL,19,Fthink they would do anything."
