OL,3,C'Lack of action over spice use' at HMP
OL,4,CParc, inquest hears
OL,6,FMr Rai described a roll call just
OL,7,Fbefore 9pm, where he witnessed nothing
OL,8,Funusual at Ross's cell and did not
OL,9,Fsmell any spice.
OL,11,FWhen he received Mr. Winter's call, it
OL,12,Ftook him about a minute to attend the
OL,13,Fcell. There, he radioed his
OL,14,Fcolleagues, who arrived shortly after,
OL,15,Fand he moved Mr. Winter to another
OL,16,Fcell.
OL,18,FHis colleague, Michael Gardiner, also
OL,19,Fgave evidence to the coroner. Although
OL,20,Fhe no longer works at HMP Parc, he'd
OL,21,Fbeen employed there since 2003.
