OL,3,C'Lack of action over spice use' at HMP
OL,4,CParc, inquest hears
OL,6,FMr Gardiner was working on another
OL,7,Fwing of B-Block when he heard a "loud
OL,8,Fcommotion," so he was already making
OL,9,Fhis way to Ross's wing when he got the
OL,10,Fcall from Mr. Rai.
OL,12,FHe described Mr. Winter as "frantic"
OL,13,Fand the wing as "very, very, loud,
OL,14,Flots of shouting from other
OL,15,Fprisoners." Gardiner described seeing
OL,16,FMr. Appleby motionless, with "quite a
OL,17,Fbit of vomit" in his mouth.
