OL,4,CParc, inquest hears
OL,6,FHe made the decision to open the cell
OL,7,Fand move Mr Appleby to the floor to
OL,8,Fcreate more space. He began CPR and
OL,9,Fcontinued to assist healthcare and
OL,10,Fparamedics when they arrived. He
OL,11,Fdescribed a defibrillator arriving at
OL,12,Fthe scene shortly after.
OL,14,FHe said there was "a lot of cannabis"
OL,15,Fin the prison at the time. He
OL,16,Fdescribed having to open vents in the
OL,17,Froof because of the smell and had once
OL,18,Fsubmitted an accident report, as he
OL,19,Fbelieved he had become ill from the
OL,20,Feffects.
